The paper deals with graph properties related to planar graphs and their drawings, which are typically studied in computational geometry (cs.CG) and discrete mathematics (cs.DM). The concept of fan-crossing free graphs is related to graph theory (cs.DS) and graph drawing (cs.GT). The paper also discusses generalizations to monotone graph properties, which are studied in algorithms and data structures (cs.DS) and social and information networks (cs.SI).
